Copied from my Yelp review written 4/30/17:  With apathetic, clumsy customer service, unnecessarily long food-to-table times, and unfresh ingredients, Parc Oasis seems to not care.  The environment is OK, if poorly air-conditioned, and some of the food is redeeming, but in my opinion this does not excuse their neglect of basic restaurant service.  Service: We did not get the water we ordered until we spoke up.  Our order for two took nearly an hour to arrive, despite there only being one other table of guests in the restaurant.  The waiter never smiled, rarely looking at us as he spoke.  He uses a smartphone to take orders, which does not help if the staff has no idea how to use it.  His eyes were glued to the device the whole time and he forgot what we ordered while tapping away on the device.  Food: The BLT was served with bruised, brown avocado.  We have never seen a restaurant try to serve such bad avocado before.  The sandwich had no sauce, making it dry.  The spaghetti was great.  The sauce was tasty, but I'm not a big fan of the meatballs.  Environment: There is a upper-midscale feel, with nice furniture and warm lighting.  The restrooms are clean, with high-tech appliances.  However, I found it difficult to enjoy the environment as, on this hot summer day, it actually felt hotter inside than outside.
